ulrike krotscheck stanford department of classics skip to navigation department of classics standford university logo header home people programs courses projects news events resources contact ulrike krotscheck position ph d classical archaeology 2008 assistant professor evergreen state college contact information ulrikek evergreen edu biography ulrike is a faculty member at the evergreen state college in olympia wa her area of interests includes archaeology particularly in the distribution of ceramics in the western mediterranean she is currently teaching greece and italy an artistic and literary odyssey which examines the architecture painted pottery and sculpture of the bronze age aegean civilizations it also investigates the roman appropriation of greek art and thought and how 15 th century italians used the ideas found in classical literature as a basis for revolutions in artistic practices and the conception of humanity email stanford classics find us on facebook address & phone search upcoming events lauren ginsberg reading the aeneid in octavia's rome 02 02 2012 luca grillo power rhetoric and irony or the end of the roman republic 02 06 2012 see more site info 2012 stanford university department of classics all rights reserved site design by chapter three login login with sunet speaker request webform for faculty stanford classics wikisite powered by drupal an open source content management system
